<br>
8 <br>
<br>
(1) initiate a rulemaking, within 30 days after the date on which the determination is made, to adopt those standards and encoding rules; and <br>
(2) publish a final rule pursuant to that rulemaking not later than 180 days after initiating the rulemaking, that will take effect 1 year after its publication. <br>
<br>
(c) NEGATIVE DETERMINATION. -- If the Commission makes a determination under subsection (a)(1) that an agreement on security system standards and encoding rules that conform to the requirements of subsections (d) and (e) has not been reached, then the Commission -- <br>
<br>
(1) in consultation with representatives described in subsection (a)(1)(A) and the Register of Copyrights, shall initiate a rulemaking, within 30 days after the date on which the determination is made, to adopt security system standards and encoding rules that conform to the requirements of subsections (d) and (e); and <br>
(2) shall publish a final rule pursuant to that rulemaking, not later than 1 year after initiating the rulemaking, that will take effect 1 year after tis publication. <br>
<br>
(d) SECURITY SYSTEM STANDARDS. -- In achieving the goals of setting open security standards that <br>
